The cycle of the seasons,
In nature’s grand design,
Each moment holds a beauty,
A spark, a light divine.

From spring’s sweet fresh beginnings,
To summer’s radiant gleam,
And autumn’s rich reflections,
Life flows like a dream.

- Ivan Turgenev
